{
  "stem": "4361.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in the early '30s, I remember-- because I was about six, seven years old-- I remember the grownups, you know, during dinner parties or when people came to visit my parents, talking about what was happening in Germany, that the government fell, and then the Reichstag was-- the burning of the Reichstag.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that there was this terrible man who had these peculiar ideas, but again, I heard the grownups say, a nation that produced Bach, Beethoven, and Brahms-- how can they believe this madman?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It shall pass.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's household was kosher.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Dairies were separate from the meat dishes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The cook was-- we always had Jewish cooks because they would know how to handle that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were generally very nice young women who came from little villages around town and who wanted to probably get some dowry together, and that's why they came to families who could afford them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they stayed for a couple of years until they amassed enough to hopefully find a man and have the dowry.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father did not wear a yamaka.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother did not have a wig, but they observed all the holidays.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Shabbat was Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Friday night, my father went to shul with the boys, with my brothers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Women did not go to shul on Friday night, at least not in Sighet, and not, not in Eastern Europe, I would assume.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Once, I remember being very reprimanded because it was Friday, and I was involved in some project in school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And lo and behold, I forgot time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as-- and-- and I-- as I came in-- and I remember my parents' home very well-- on the foyer, I could see the dining room, and I saw they were already sitting at the table.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
